articles.title: Miller beer destroyed over High Life's 'Champagne of Beers' label - USA TODAY
articles.description: Beer and Champagne don't always mix in Europe. 98 cases of Miller High Life were destroyed at the order of Belgium officials. Here's why.
articles.content:
Authorities in Europe crushed  literally  more than 2,300 cans of Miller High Life because the beer is labelled "The Champagne of Beers."
